But I really want to emphasize how difficult it is for those who have bipolar when people misuse the term mania to describe elevated moods and euphoria. And one of the main hallmarks of mania is it lasting consecutively for more than a week, usually for months

But it’s not the same thing, and with BPD it’s related to outside factors, such as their relationships and something occurring. But again, manic is a diagnostic term and shouldn’t be used to describe loosely unless you do have manic episodes
